President Trump met with members of the Republican Study Committee in the Oval Office to discuss healthcare and the improvements being made to the American Health Care Act. The President expressed his support for the bill and criticized the media for not giving it a fair chance. He also stated that Obamacare is dead and that the new healthcare plan will be fantastic. The President thanked the committee members, who had previously been undecided or opposed to the bill, for now supporting it. He highlighted the importance of allowing states to have more control over their healthcare programs and mentioned that insurance companies will be able to offer new plans to take care of people at all levels. The President acknowledged that it will take some time for the new healthcare plan to fully take effect, but he emphasized that it will be better than Obamacare.